# Day 4 – Note Taker 📝

## What it does
A terminal-based note taking app that lets you
add notes and view all saved notes — persisted
to a local text file between sessions.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3 (built-in only)
- File I/O (open, read, write)

## How to run
python note_taker.py

## What I learned
- File handling with open() in append and read mode
- While True loops for interactive menus
- Try/except for FileNotFoundError
- Structuring code
